    "question_id" : 31038250,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>There are two different ways you can add/override spring properties on the command line.</p>\n<h3>Option 1: Java System Properties (VM Arguments)</h3>\n<p>It's important that the -D parameters are before your application.jar\notherwise they are not recognized.</p>\n<pre><code>java -jar -Dspring.profiles.active=prod application.jar\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Option 2: Program arguments</h3>\n<pre><code>java -jar application.jar --spring.profiles.active=prod --spring.config.location=c:\\config\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
